author: trparky
text:
I don't agree with Joe Biden on a lot of things. Hell, I think many of his policies are the main cause of many of our economic troubles but I have to admit that perhaps there's something I'd agree with him on and that it needs to stop.

According to Bloomberg, Biden called for this...

> In his State of the Union address Tuesday, President Joe Biden touted his administration’s efforts to [crack down](https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-02-08/biden-calls-for-antitrust-measures-to-rein-in-power-of-big-tech?sref=rY0z5sRB) on so-called “junk fees,” or charges that raise the prices of items like concert tickets, hotel rooms and internet service.   
>  
>He urged Congress to require online ticket sellers to disclose the full costs upfront, eliminate cancellation penalties for phone and web services and ban fees that airlines charge for families to sit together and that hotels tack on for being resorts. Biden also said his administration will require airlines to disclose full ticket prices upfront and push banks to reduce “excessive” [credit card late fees](https://www.consumerfinance.gov/about-us/newsroom/cfpb-proposes-rule-to-rein-in-excessive-credit-card-late-fees/). 

Someone better go check Hell, it might be frozen over.
